article.headline: Denver 68, Arkansas State 53
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- J.J. Montgomery scored 18 points and Kim Adams pulled down 12 rebounds Monday night as Arkansas State cruised past Arkansas Tech 68-53 in an exhibition game. Tevoris Thompson had 12 points for the Indians, and Antonio Rambo scored 11. Rambo also had three steals for an Indians team that forced 19 turnovers -- 12 of them steals. ASU made only 4 of 23 shots from 3-point range, but the Indians were disciplined at the foul line, sinking 16 of 19. ASU shot 40.7 percent from the field on the night, compared to 35.4 percent for Arkansas Tech. Josh Jones led Tech with 16 point and Jordan LaRue scored 10. Tech made 1 of 8 3s and sank 18 of 28 from the line.
